<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does book fulfilment cost for an online bookstore at 30 orders per day?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Approximately $320-410 per month at 30 orders/day. Calculation: shipping at $0.50/order × 900 = $450, but with low-AOV book volume discount drops to ~$0.36 effective rate. Storage of 1 m³ × $15 = $15. Exact figure delivered within one business day after the first 15-minute consultation — we need your average order value, number of titles, and average parcel weight."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you track books in your WMS — by ISBN or by internal SKU?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our WMS handles both codes simultaneously. ISBN is the primary international identifier and is bound to the storage cell. Publisher's internal SKU is stored as an alias — orders can be submitted in either format. At receiving we scan the ISBN barcode from the cover, verify against the print run record, and assign to a fixed shelf address. The dashboard shows real-time inventory by ISBN at any moment."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you accept small print runs from self-published authors — from 50 copies?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The minimum print run we accept is 20 copies per title. We work with self-published authors printing 50-500 copies per run. There is a separate pricing tier for low-volume operations — the monthly minimum is $114 (5,000 UAH equivalent). This breaks even at approximately 250 orders per month or a series of B2B pre-orders for the same title."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you package books to prevent damage to cover corners?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Standard packaging: bubble wrap around the book, then a rigid book-format cardboard mailer (B5 for standard editions, A4 for large format). The spine is positioned in the middle of the mailer to absorb impact during transit. For gift editions and art books — additional kraft paper layer and branded ribbon. Multi-book orders go in MTP-branded box or your custom branded packaging with paper void-fill so books do not collide during shipping."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you prepare for September school season and Black Friday peaks?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Ukrainian book market peaks are August-September (textbooks, school literature, children's books) and November-December (Black Friday, holiday gifts, corporate orders). Four weeks before each peak we plan volume with each client, replenish packaging stock, schedule additional shifts. Warehouse capacity is up to 6,000 orders per day. December 2024 peak averaged 9,200 orders per day across our client base with zero downtime."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you handle cross-border shipping of books to Poland, Czechia, Canada, USA?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, via Nova Poshta International. Ukrainian and Russian-language literature is actively exported to diaspora communities in Poland, Czechia, Germany, Canada, and the United States. We prepare CN23 customs forms (books carry 0% import duty in most destination countries), handle export documentation, and hand off to NP International. Transit times: Poland 5-7 business days, Germany 7-10, Czechia 6-8, Canada 14-21, USA 14-25. Pricing depends on weight and country."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you process book returns damaged in shipping?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Return arrives at warehouse → we unpack → photograph condition → check for damage (bent corners, marks, spine creases, water damage). Books in good condition return to shelf inventory automatically within 24 hours. Damaged copies go to a dedicated zone for publisher decision: write off, donate to charity, sell at discount as 'second condition'. Return processing fee is $0.57 with photo documentation — critical for resolving customer disputes ('the cover was perfect when shipped, here is the photo')."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you integrate with Horoshop and KeyCRM — the dominant Ukrainian platforms for book retailers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, natively. Horoshop is the most popular SaaS storefront platform for Ukrainian book retailers. KeyCRM is the typical order management system. Integration via prebuilt connector takes 2 hours. Orders from your store admin flow into our WMS automatically, delivery status is returned to your dashboard. We also support WooCommerce, OpenCart, Shopify, Magento, Prom.ua API, and Rozetka API."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can international publishers use your warehouse to enter the Ukrainian and CIS book market?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Through a foreign trade contract with MTP, your inventory clears Ukrainian customs once at import. After that you operate as a local seller in the Ukrainian market: integrations with Rozetka, Prom, Kasta, Kasta, settlements in UAH, delivery via Nova Poshta. Onboarding takes 21 business days from contract signing to first shipment. Suitable for publishers from EU, North America, or CIS who want to test the Ukrainian book market without opening a local entity."}}]}</script>
