    <p>The Ukrainian book market in 2026 is going through two simultaneous transformations. The first is the rise of self-publishing — bloggers, subject-matter experts, and children's illustrators printing their own books in runs of 100-500 copies and selling through Instagram, Telegram, and Yakaboo. The second is the strengthening of niche independent publishers filling segments previously dominated by major players: translations from rare languages, specialized literature, religious editions.</p>
    <p>Both segments need a fulfilment partner because operating their own warehouse is not economically justified at the 100-500 orders per month volume. Outsourcing logistics to Yakaboo or KSD as external sales channels means giving up 30-40% of margin. Maintaining their own warehouse means paying at least $850 per month in rent plus staff plus WMS even when shipping only 200 orders. MTP closes this gap: we accept volume from 250+ orders per month (monthly minimum $114) and scale to 6,000 orders per day without the publisher hiring additional headcount.</p>
    <p>Separately — the cross-border export segment. Ukrainian diaspora in Poland (~1.5 million), Czechia (~150,000), Germany (~1 million since 2022), Canada (~1.4 million), and the USA (~1 million) is an active reading audience. Publishers working with this audience directly typically derive 5-15% of annual revenue from cross-border channels. Streamlined logistics with CN23 documentation, NP International integration, and FX-aware billing makes this channel scalable without daily manual work per shipment.</p>
